{
  "texts": [
    "Characterized by their massive number of parameters, usually between a billion and a trillion, these models excel in generating coherent, contextually relevant text over lengthy passages.",
    "Their foundational neural networks, which are key elements in the various attention heads in transformers, encompass tens to hundreds of millions of parameters, necessitating extensive training data.The central feature of the transformer is the self-attention mechanism, which enables a word to compute its context by checking the relevance of all other words in the sentence, see Fig. 2.",
    "This is done using Query (Q), Key (K), and Value (V) vectors.",
    "Herein, the query represents the current word or token one attention mechanism is focusing on and determines how much attention should be paid to other tokens.",
    "The key represents all tokens in the input and scores each token's relevance to the current focus."
  ]
}